## RULE: Deploy boundaries — cms-editor is a separate Python Worker
**ID:** rule_deploy_boundaries | **Priority:** ALWAYS

Three separate deploy targets — never conflate:
1. IAM Worker:      npm run deploy:full  (JS/TS, wrangler.production.toml)
2. cms-editor:      pywrangler deploy    (Python/Pyodide, separate wrangler.toml)
3. R2 frontend:     npm run build:analytics then R2 sync

pywrangler ≠ wrangler — different CLI, installed via: uv tool install workers-py
Before any cms-editor deploy: verify uv --version first.
Forbidden: marking a task done after /health-only response.

